"Careful what you do, as you may be next" has rather chilling connotations for me here in the UK. We have a show here called "Love Island", part dating show part reality TV.

This show has been rocked by suicide. 3 former contestants and, in the last week, one of the hosts. It's causing a massive stink here about a TV show's duty of care for the people appearing on them, how they are represented in this so-called "reality TV" and what role the media played in these people's deaths.
